blog.name: hikennydesign
blog.title: HiKenny Design & Illustration
blog.description:
Hi, Im Kenny, I make art. Preferably for money. Im from and still reside in Portland Oregon. Im primarily a digital artist. I work on an iPad Pro, using an Apple Pencil. I draw in Procreate, sketchbook pro, and make vector illustrations through Inkpad. Born at the end of 82. Ive been making art, one way or another, my whole life. I went to college for a better part of my 20’s. Started in a Clackamas Community College, enjoyed foolishly concentrating on art. A few credits short of an general associates degree, I went on to Pacific Northwest College of Art. Where I studied illustration and got a Bachelors of fine art in such, graduating in 2012. I’m freelance, so I make art in between a day job. I’ve worked for a interesting variety of industries. I had a set of illustrated nudes featured at Club Sesso in October 2010. I was featured in a limited run magazine call IWANTYOURSKULL issue 9. I worked for the adult industry making advertisements, signs, and fliers. Worked for a lot of cam girls making headers and water makes for photos. I’ve made art for bands for fliers, lapel pins, and T-shirt’s. I’ve designed tons of tattoos. Most recently I’ve been working for Oregon legal Cannabis industry making illustrations, info graphics, banners, advertisements, branding, vector design for screen printing layouts, and even a bit of building layouts plans for OLCC license requirements.

I enjoy making art for people who enjoy what I do. Get some money together, let’s chat. Until then, enjoy my work, follow to keep up on my shenanigans, and be sure share HiKenny Design with your friends and loved ones. Kenny is for the people.

summary: i found a beautiful picture of a model wearing a red gown and used it as inspiration to create different characters . I haven’t...
caption:
i found a beautiful picture of a model wearing a red gown and used it as inspiration to create different characters . I haven’t done that kind of exercise in a long time and forgot how fun it is!

In my case the first design shapes I draw are usually not as pushes as they could be. I almost think of it like getting a bad drawing out of your system. Then after that pushing shapes becomes so much more easy!

You can find close up versions of the designs on my INSTAGRAM page

summary: Important message! I'm opening request for the first time~
body:
Important message! I’m opening request for the first time~

Yes! You heard me fuckers! come at me with some delicious requests! I would prefer if they’re mario bros related (because I’m doing a sort of mario theme month) but if you don’t like it/just don’t want to, you can request ALMOST, and I repeat, ALMOST everything. This means if somethings makes me uncomfortable I have all the rights to deny your request. That being said GIMME SOMETHING TO DRAW~♡
